1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,000
I built a capsule wardrobe twice.

2
00:00:03,000 --> 00:00:06,000
Both times it failed.

3
00:00:06,000 --> 00:00:10,000
First time — 37-piece rule, donated two bags of clothes.
Still wore the same six outfits.

4
00:00:10,000 --> 00:00:13,500
Second time — 30-piece challenge,
photographed the whole grid.

5
00:00:13,500 --> 00:00:16,500
Still froze at 7 AM wondering what to wear
for a client call.

6
00:00:16,500 --> 00:00:20,000
The problem wasn't the clothes.
It was the occasions.

7
00:00:20,000 --> 00:00:23,500
Magazine capsules are for someone else's life —
coffee meetings, gallery openings, dinner parties.

8
00:00:23,500 --> 00:00:27,500
My actual week? WFH Monday through Wednesday.
Gym Thursday morning.

9
00:00:27,500 --> 00:00:31,000
Client visit Thursday afternoon.
Casual weekends.

10
00:00:31,000 --> 00:00:34,000
One weirdly formal obligation.
No universal list covers that without dead weight.

11
00:00:34,000 --> 00:00:38,000
Stop asking "does this spark joy?"
Start asking: which occasion does this cover?

12
00:00:38,000 --> 00:00:42,000
If a piece only works for one occasion
you have twice a year, it's not earning its space.

13
00:00:42,000 --> 00:00:46,000
If it stretches across three weekly contexts?
It's doing real work. Keep it.

14
00:00:46,000 --> 00:00:50,000
That matrix — piece, occasion, frequency —
AI solves it in seconds.

15
00:00:50,000 --> 00:00:53,500
I cataloged my actual wardrobe,
told Dripmatiq my real week,

16
00:00:53,500 --> 00:00:57,000
and it found gaps I couldn't see.

17
00:00:57,000 --> 00:01:00,500
Five pieces covered WFH but nothing
for the gym-to-errands transition.

18
00:01:00,500 --> 00:01:04,500
And that navy midi skirt I thought was too formal?
It pairs with a linen shirt and flats

19
00:01:04,500 --> 00:01:08,000
for exactly the casual-weekend look
I'd been reaching for and not finding.

20
00:01:08,000 --> 00:01:12,000
The capsule wasn't built.
It was found.

21
00:01:12,000 --> 00:01:15,500
Most people already own a functional wardrobe —
they just can't see it.

22
00:01:15,500 --> 00:01:19,000
Too much noise.
No system mapping pieces to real life.

23
00:01:19,000 --> 00:01:23,000
Your pieces. Your life.
Mapped. Working.

24
00:01:23,000 --> 00:01:26,500
